<article>
    <h3>
        What happens in information technology management?
    </h3>
    <div>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Determining business requirements for IT systems
            </li>
            <li>
                Managing IT budgets and costs
            </li>
            <li>
                Monitoring safety and compliance
            </li>
            <li>
                Controlling system and network security
            </li>
            <li>
                Implemented new software hardware and data systems
            </li>
            <li>
                Providing technical or help desk support
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h3>So what does all this do? </h3>

    <p>
        Determines Information Technology strategies and goals for the business and ensure they are implemented.
    </p>

    <p>
        Processes, Software Hardware, and Systems using a business environment to conduct day-to-day operations.
    </p>

    <h3>Advantages of Information technology management</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>
            There are very few business processes that do not depend or cannot benefit from information technology
        </li>
        <li>
            Information technology management allows businesses to manage their data efficiently regardless of its form
        </li>
        <li>
            Information technology management allow employees to be more productive but it can also be tailor to suit a
            company's specific needs
        </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Information technology management have several career paths as it has best of both worlds that is business and
        information technology and it requires strong analytical and mathematical problem solving skills
    <ol>
        <li>
            Project management
        </li>
        <li>
            Data security and role management
        </li>
        <li>
            Data organisation and analysis
        </li>
        <li>
            System analysis design and Organisation
        </li>
        <li>
            Software and Hardware assessment
        </li>
    </ol>
    </p>

    Important points:

    <div>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Workers in information technology management are considered part of skilled workforce and sometimes
                referred
                to as knowledge workers
            </li>
            <li>
                In addition to typical information technology skill set a career in information technology management
                requires strong interpersonal skills, management ability and collaborative problem solving skills
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <p>
        Common roles in information technology management
    <ul>
        <li>
            Software developers
        </li>
        <li>
            Database & system administrators
        </li>
        <li>
            Information Security analyst
        </li>
    </ul>
    </p>
